tal writings collectively transform our understanding of that tradition. Santoro makes clear the shared ethical and aesthetic commitments that nourished a transatlantic community whose contribution to mainstream literature and cultural productions, including postmodernism, is still being felt today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian fiction (French)xHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aCanadian fiction (French)xHistory and criticismxQuebec (Province). 0aCanadian fiction (French)xWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aExperimental fiction, Canadian (French)xHistory and criticism. 0aExperimental fiction, FrenchxHistory and criticism. 0aExperimental fiction, French-CanadianxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminist fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminist fiction, Canadian (French)xHistory and criticism. 0aFrench fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aFrench fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench-Canadian fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aFrench-Canadian fictionxHistory and criticismxQuébec (Province). 0aFrench-Canadian fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench-Canadian fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench-Canadian fictionzQuébec (Province)xHistory and criticism. 0aInvention (Rhetoric)xHistoryx20th century. 0aInvention (Rhetoric)xHistoryy20th century. 0aRoman canadien-françaisxHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aRoman canadien-françaisxHistoire et critiquexQuébec (Province). 0aRoman expérimental canadien-françaisxHistoire et critique. 0aRoman expérimental françaisxHistoire et critique. 0aRoman françaisxHistoire et critiquex20e sièclexFrankreichxFranzösischxQuébec (Provinz)xQuébec. 0aRoman féministe canadien-françaisxHisto